    <item>
      <title>Where The Heart Trails</title>
      <author> PuffyBun </author>
      <link>https://www.scribblehub.com/series/1238415/where-the-heart-trails/</link>
      <comments>https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1238415-where-the-heart-trails/chapter/1238502/#comments</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">8a71c55d61c8ca4a6ab39823e1b56719ea6499cf</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 28 Sep 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ah, The trail of love for Tricia Davenport has long since been deserted. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The Carriage that rode along that road had long perished into the abyss of pain and divorce and was nothing more than a smattering of pieces. Real love was not to be found. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;At least that's what Tricia thought. Hard emphasis on Thought. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Being a live-in maid is only tough when you have worked for bless'ed Gabrielle for 9ish years. This woman will snap and bark like an angsty chihuahua whenever She doesn't get her way and..well..Ivan her nephew was her and Tricia's only bungee cord from swan diving straight into insanity over what the other did. Ivan's presence merely reduced it to just a teeter totter on the brink of insanity.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;It is absolutely safe to say that neither saw it their way and Frankly it was getting old. Real, old. As the days stretched on, it became more evident that Tricia's work ethic was on life alert, at least in Gabrielle's opinion.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Gabrielle swore up and down that Tricia was just being lazy. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ivan Thought things were going swimmingly with a few tiffs, mistakes here and there. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Tricia wished she had a tall never-ending glass of Whiskey and Gabrielle would shut up already. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;When Gabrielle finally had just about had it with Tricia's shenanigans and snapped like a brittle twig in the middle of November; She upped and hired a new maid with her precious money!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;A Gorgeous Maid. A Capable Maid! A maid That wasn't Tricia!&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;But Right off the bat, something felt off to Tricia...Really off.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Why is it, As soon as She came around, She's got these 'weird' heart problems?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;As soon as She came around, the stagnant pool of lust and longing akin to gasoline was set a lit. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;As soon as she came around and stuck around, Those heart strings that she was sure had shriveled up and croaked? No longer weren't in a way She did. not. understand. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;But amidst all these problems the doctor swore he couldn't diagnose, There were two promises Tricia made to herself.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;To always care for her prized Horses and to never, ever fall for the love bullshit. It was the bachelor life from here on out.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Or..was it?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1238415-where-the-heart-trails/chapter/1238502/"&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;Chapter 1 – A New Job!&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&lt;b&gt;Chapter 1 - &lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;A New Job!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Gabrielle, The Slender older woman Sat directly across this behemoth of a desk from Myra. Her blonde hair was pulled back into a ponytail that looked too tight, dragging the temples of her forehead back with it. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She donned a sleeveless indigo colored dress of smooth Satin fabric. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;(Where in the &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;blasted hell&lt;/em&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;is Ivan and Tricia?? They are &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;late.) &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Gabrielle &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;thought. She curled her frail hand tight into a fist while her other hand rose and sat her slim golden-rimmed reading glasses upon her face properly. ( I expected Tricia To be late but &lt;em&gt;Ivan&lt;/em&gt;?? Usually he is right on the money..)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Let's see.." Gabrielle spoke, her eyes glazing over Myra's resume. "We've discussed history..experience..live-in expectations..Tricia and Ivan should be down in a matter of a minute to discuss the further details." Gabrielle said, taking the thin stack of papers, straightening them, putting them on the table.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Myra had her Back straight, Her Shoulders back, her chin up and poker face on. "Yes Mam." Myra said as She sat still. (Oh my GOODNESS..! I hope I get this job..&lt;em&gt;I need this job, &lt;/em&gt;I sure need a break from city life..) Myra could barely quell this strange cocktail of excitement and anxiety in her chest, but her dad taught her one thing, while negotiating anything, don't you let those feelings show..&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Her eyes started to dance across the room to distract herself.. they had not earlier for fear that she wouldn't be offered this job at all and that this interview would be like all the others. But, now that they were waiting on some people to get here to solidify the deal,- She felt like She had this job snug in the bag..at least; almost.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The room was rather small and quaint, with a Mossy green wallpaper and warm-colored wood trim lined along the ceiling. The trim &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;was such a light color that it almost looked golden. The 4 tall white paned windows showed the ever-stretching valley of grass and trees, the sun playing peek-a-boo through them. Her eyes shifted from them to the Table where they sat. The wooden table that stretched between them looked like it was made of maple wood. It had A deep mesmerizing chocolate color; the groves in the wood were swimming. (Expensive..for sure.) She sighed softly, both briefly enjoying the silence and the table's glory.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Gabrielle exhaled deeply as her head tilted to the door like it was on a broken hinge. She stared at the door, then her eyes darted to the young &lt;span style="text-decoration:underline"&gt;to-be&lt;/span&gt; maid. She eyed her from a distance. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She sat so poised and ladylike in her fitted, long-sleeved, merlot-toned velvet dress that was l&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;ined with a beige-colored lace lapel, intricately bordering the neck's hem. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;It screamed of autumn fashion; not of this early August. It looked kind of tattered, slightly wrinkled; possibly well loved or bought second hand. She was busy gazing at the table calmly from her chair. Her skin resembled it closely..It was a warm colored brown that resembled rich bourbon. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Myra lifted her head to Gabrielle. Her long, curly, wavy strands of black hair became apparent- they looked very striking next to the soft sunlit rays from the window, especially next to her hazel, turquoise colored eyes. Her lips were very plump and pronounced.. How symmetrical her face was..her skinny arms..What a petite figure she had. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The same One that Gabrielle had when she was much, much younger..&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Myra honey. How old are you?" &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Myra thought She had already answered this question. "Oh..I am 27."&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Oh goodness me." Gabrielle dryly chuckled, placing her pen down on the wooden table with a tap. She curled her hand that resembled a dragons underneath her bony chin before responding further.  "You're almost there." Gabrille's voice rang out like a twinkling bell when she said that, waving her pale white finger nail that was a ruby red color at her. She smiled coyly as she folded her hands together and locked them in front of her, neatly laying them on the table they sat across. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Almost..There?" Myra questioned, keeping her hands still in her lap. Her well manicured eyebrow poked up as she awaited more clarification on this 'almost there.' She didn't know why but the aura in the room had changed slightly. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"The undesirable age," Gabrielle said with a sad grunt. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Her sly smile slash pout stretched across her thin pink lips. "The age where..men don't come as easy any more..gifts..favors..you know.." She said motioning her hands in a circular motion in the air before crashing them back down to the table. "Things dry right up..hair..skin..bah!" &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Myra disagreed completely..She saw how her mother aged..Still beautiful even with all her wrinkles that resembled water rippling.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; Gabrielle saw the disagreement grow on the corners of her lips. Myra watched Gabrielle's eyes speak for themselves, Them squinting.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Myra dry chuckled, swishing her curly wild hair over her shoulder to the rest of her strands. "I..I disagree Ms. Gabrielle." She started. "I think losing your youth is a necessary matter in the cycle.. you sound sad when you speak about it..Sure having your youth is fun..but there's still fun to be had when you're older!..&lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;plus&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;..I'm not that old." She finished with a tiny beaming smile.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Hm." Gabrielle sounded so dissatisfied. whatever fake light that was in her eyes promptly died. "You disagree?" She said slowly leaning forward now in her chair. She opened her mouth to say something, but was interrupted when She heard the door open and close shut to the left of her. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;There Tricia, Her Current Maid waltzed halfway into the room with zero urgency. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Myra's eyes pinned onto Tricia. She stared At the tall, olive-skinned woman. She felt a spark of something jolt through her. (wow..so beautiful.!) She could immediately tell she spent probably..most of her days outside despite being a live in maid. Her hair was a ginger color, tied up into a tried-to-be neat bun.  She had big, voluptuous&lt;span class="fc6omth regular_f1jfh96c f18ev72d"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;breasts, toned thighs from what she could tell; even through the dark colored slacks that they wore. She had loads of freckles like her cheeks had been sprayed with a freckle paint gun. Tall, sizing up the door. Her shoulders were broad in her white blouse. The sleeves were rolled up past her elbows, cinching and clinging onto her musculy arms. Her hand nearly swallowed up the doorknob she was holding!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; "My bad we late. We was tryin to figure out what was wrong wit da washer." &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Gabrielle snapped her entire body in the chair to Tricia. Her mouth widened from the stance it took before! &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Tricia leaned her head back, preparing for the full blast of whatever it was that was about to fly out of her mouth, hand readied on the crystal door knob to use it as a shield, but Ivan squished beside Tricia into the room and did some very quick damage control. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"My deepest, OUR Deepest Apologies! We Were Trying to Fix the Washer, WE got so invested into the problem we just lost track of time.! Sorry, sorry let's get this underway now shall we!" He nodded to Myra, Then nodded to Gabrielle, then Tricia. Tricia shifted her eyes. With that, He swiftly shut Gabrielle up and patted Tricia's shoulder. He made a bee line to Myra. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Hello There, I'm Ivan. So nice to meet you." Ivan said quickly. He wore a simple white blouse and loose maroon colored slacks. His handshake was firm and His long honey brown jumpy locks stopped at his shoulders complete with bangs that hung over his forehead like curtains. He was slender..but not too slender. Built with a small chest and toned arms. Not too tall and mature in the face with an aftershave. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Told ya." Tricia smirked At Gabrielle.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Gabrille huffed, kind of agitated from already being interrupted. "Thought you'd be busy trying to tell your right foot from your left.."&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"&lt;strong&gt;DON'T&lt;/strong&gt;!" Ivan halted them both with his loud, hearty voice. "&lt;span style="text-decoration:underline"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Don't&lt;/em&gt; you two  throw coal on that fire&lt;/span&gt;. Tricia; Greet Myra please." Ivan Said Taking a seat beside Gabrielle.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Tricia deeply sighed tucking her hot response down somewhere in her body and finally looked over into Myra direction. (holy..) Her eyes pin locked onto hers. She got some pep in her step then. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Nice ta Meet ya Ms.Myra.." Tricia said, reaching her hand out to her.  She softly shook it. They stared at each other as if they were reading each other's minds! (Wee &lt;strong&gt;Doggy&lt;/strong&gt;..look it there.&lt;em&gt;.fine..fine..fine.&lt;/em&gt;) Tricia thought, trying so hard not to lick her lips. It didn't matter What Myra did now, She was on her Radar. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Eventually Myra's dazed look turned into a smile..(Her eyes are green..the same color as my mothers..! pretty..) She internally swooned. It was like Tricia sensed her internal swoon, her head tilted..(mmm.) and Ivan coughed dramatically..(The girl hasn't even started yet!!) He thought. Gabrielle just rubbed her forehead like there were a million bugs on it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Anyway&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;," Gabrille swished her hand in the air over to the empty chair next to Myra. "hurry up, Take a seat so we can sign this paperwork and Have Ms.Myra here up and working." She croaked.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Y-yes Mam." Tricia said absent mindedly. Tricia slowly released her hand as if Myra was a princess. She didn't take her eyes off of her for even a second as she struggled to find the seat of her chair. She had to remind herself that she couldn't just stare at Tricia the whole time. She couldn't wait to talk to her. Tricia sat perplexed over how in the hell did they get this girl up into this house, amongst &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;other things&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;..&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Gabrille made a woosh noise with her mouth, fully not expecting nor believing the plesentries from her. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Ivan quickly looked over the paperwork and took out his pen, immediately scratching something out on it. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Ivan. What are you doing." Gabrille asked condescendingly as She smirked her lips and rose her dark blonde wrinkled heavy eyebrows and eyelids at him. She glanced down to the paperwork. Her eyes widened big as hell. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Instead of the Sixty dollar weekly pay, let's make this a proper Two hundred!" &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Myra had to pick her mental jaw up off the floor. (Two. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Hundred&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;...!!!)  Myra's face was glowing..!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Gabrille leaned back into her seat, astonished. (Two. &lt;i&gt;Hundred&lt;/i&gt;...!!!)  Gabrielle's face was blank and sprinkled with vexation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Tricia yelled "&lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;haha!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; Gon get yo money!" before chuckling and relaxing back into her chair. Her yelling made an audible echo as she did. Myra got scared the second she yelled but couldn't help but giggle at her after. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Yes. That's more than enough for you right? Ms.Myra?" Ivan said, flipping his head between all three of them eagerly.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She gulped almost not wanting to answer. That is the most money she had ever seen in her whole career. To have that much money would mean she could finally save for a house..a car..maybe even finally afford that exorbitant cost of college tuition. Deep down she didn't want them to change the amount..but felt like it wasn't smart to argue.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Her wide hazel eyes refused to look at Gabrielle now out of fear, so She looked at Ivans slanted maroon ones instead. She used them to scream a resounding &lt;/span&gt;&lt;b&gt;yes&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Thank you.." She said meekly, anxiously twiddling and pulling at her fingers underneath the table. She slightly bowed her head. Her heart was racing a mile a minute now. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Ivan, No." Gabrielle said starkly. If i pay &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;her&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; two hundred, I have to pay Tricia two hundred, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;and&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; I have to buy a different brand of makeup &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;and&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; I won't be able to take that ski trip this year in the winter time-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"What do you mean? We have more than enough in the budget? If it will cause problems for you and fairness is an issue then I'll pay it but we already pay Tricia two hundred a week." &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"Tricia? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;b&gt;When&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; did we start paying Tricia two hundred a week?? She hasn't even hung the laundry out to dry yet, nor did she bring me my morning &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;ma-mo-sa&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;." &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Tricia went to open her mouth, Ivan put up one finger. Tricia sandwhiched her lips closed and shook her head.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"First, we fixed the washer, Second, 5 months ago, third, I told her not to because you like to ask for another..and then another.." &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Hmph&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;. I'm a grown ass woman. I'll drink as much as I'd like, Ivan; stop meddling." &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;He raised his hand up in a stop motion. "To bring us back to the point." He pointed at the paperwork. "I'm going to pay Ms.Myra Two hundred off rip, a second raise effective..in 2 months, an additional two hundred upon evaluation...there. Good enough?" He said looking at them both. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Myra was as frozen as an ice sickle except her hands, her body language screaming yes. Tricia just kept slowly nodding. Gabrille sat still, unimpressed and arms crossed. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"If you're paying, fine. You're hired. Don't screw up." She said standing up from the desk and whisking herself out of the room after scribbling some signature. Tricia started clapping. "Woop!!"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Myra nearly imploded watched Ivan sign that paperwork. She heard her fathers voice echo in her ear. (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Doesn't mean anything until its signed..Doesn't mean anything until its signed..doesn't mean anything until its signed&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;..) He finally finished and promptly held it out to Myra. She shot out of her seat like a geyser. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;He shook her trembling hand the second She came over. "Welcome! I'm so glad you came to work for us. I'll show you around the place and show you your room!-"&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;"How about it?" &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
