      <title>To Be An Heir</title>
      <author> LightNovelNovice </author>
      <link>https://www.scribblehub.com/series/1229450/to-be-an-heir/</link>
      <comments>https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1229450-to-be-an-heir/chapter/1229452/#comments</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">c80bd195dbd431be2e73471a5f270b9ff6cf99fb</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 06 Oct 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;What happens when a manly prince's true nature is exposed?&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This story prominently features romance and drama between young adults in a fantasy academy setting. Lots of gender bending, complex emotions, and internal struggles are present throughout the story.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Currently no established upload schedule. :(&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1229450-to-be-an-heir/chapter/1229452/"&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;Arranged Marriage [1]&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;div class="wi_authornotes"&gt; &lt;div&gt; &lt;div class="p-avatar-wrap"&gt;&lt;a class="avatar has-link" href="/profile/103629/lightnovelnovice/"&gt;&lt;img id="acc_ava_change profile" alt="" src="https://cdn.scribblehub.com/avatar/s/25/ava_103629_1724372118.jpg"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="an_username"&gt;&lt;a href="/profile/103629/lightnovelnovice/"&gt;LightNovelNovice&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div style="clear: both;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="wi_authornotes_body"&gt;  Warning! This chapter contains domestic abuse!&lt;br /&gt;Hope you enjoy, regardless!&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The clang of steel on steel rings throughout the training yard. Flashes of steel reflect sunlight as an intense spar takes place. The boy: a cocky youth with a handsome face. The girl: a determined fighter with a tomboy aesthetic. They're both sweating profusely.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Give it up already, Cassy!" The boy says with a laugh.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Cassandra doesn't waver in the face of the silver haired boy's taunting. She pulls her sword back only to swipe at him from the other side. The boy raises his blade and parries the attack. Cassandra grits her teeth in frustration as she goes for another slash from the side. Again, it's parried effortlessly by the boy.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Can't you give it your all, Andromeda?!" Cassandra shouts angrily.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Andromeda laughs loudly, his deep baritone voice filling the training yard. Cassandra tries to take advantage of his outburst, but he deflects her blade without missing a beat. Andromeda's lighthearted smile shifts into a dark frown. He reveals the gap between them.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"This is why I don't get serious, Cassandra." Andromeda's tone is low and threatening.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Cassandra helplessly backpedals as a flurry of strikes rain down upon her. She can hardly keep up with the assault. She feels one of her silver hairs fall away as Andromeda's blade grazes her neck. She trips, falling onto her back. Andromeda presses his sword's blade to her neck.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The two of them look at one another. Cassandra's chest rises and falls with the exertion of the fight, but Andromeda isn't even winded. Andromeda watches her coldly as hot tears start to pour from her eyes. Cassandra sobs quietly as Andromeda retracts his sword.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Remember the gap between us, dear sister."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Andromeda turns away from Cassandra without sparing her a second glance. A maid hands Andromeda a cloth to wipe away his sweat as he leaves the training yard.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;She glances pityingly at Cassandra, but doesn't speak up for the girl. Andromeda hands the maid the dirtied cloth.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"...Your father wants to see you, Lord Andromeda," The maid says quietly.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The maid's softly spoken words have an unseen effect on Andromeda. The perfect mask of nobility cracks, and his lip twitches ever so slightly. The maid doesn't notice this.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"I understand," Andromeda replies coldly in his usual baritone.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Andromeda and his personal maid walk back into the estate. The spacious corridors are lit by countless magically powered lamps. Exceptional painting and exquisite sculptures decorate the manor's interior. Andromeda pauses at a particular painting. He turns, looking up at it.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The painting depicts a stoic silver haired man with rugged features. His face exudes a sort of stony seriousness befitting a duke. Standing beside him is a dark haired woman with a gentle smile. In front of the couple are two children. One is a boy with short silver hair and a bright smile. The other is a long silver haired girl with a dour frown. Andromeda sighs.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"We best move along, Lord Andromeda. The Duke seemed... antsy."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Another small crack forms in Andromeda's emotional mask.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Yes, of course."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Andromeda's bedroom is a luxurious affair. The huge bed is adorned with the finest silk bedding. The windows are framed with golden trim. The suit of armor resting on the armor stand is the finest money can buy. Everything here is fit for a prince.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The maid carefully undresses Andromeda with practiced ease. Andromeda does his best to stare straight ahead as his personal maid removes his training clothes. He can feel her soft hands brush along his skin as she works. She remains professional despite the intimacy.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;It takes a few minutes for her to dress Andromeda up in formal clothing fit for meeting with a duke. She turns the mirror to face him, and a third small crack forms in his mask as he appraises his reflection. The broad shouldered silver haired boy in the mirror looks perfect. Andromeda knows better, though. He can see the hollow black holes in the boy's grey eyes.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Let us be off, Lord Andromeda," The maid urges.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Andromeda doesn't bother replying to her words. He follows her through the corridors toward his father's study. The quiet echoes of their footsteps punctuate the immense scale of the estate. It feels quite empty to Andromeda.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;They arrive at the heavy oaken doors leading into Duke Ashfey's study. The maid gently knocks on the door before announcing her purpose.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"I have brought Lord Andromeda, Your Grace."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Andromeda's usually flawless mask is filled with hairline fractures as he anticipates meeting with his father. The familiar sound of Duke Ashfey's deep gravely voice comes from beyond the door.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"You're dismissed. Please enter, Andromeda."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The maid bows to Andromeda before quickly departing. Andromeda reaches out with both of his hands, and pushes open the doors to his father's study. The study is filled with bookshelves containing important books and documents related to the dukedom. An impressive stained glass window bears the Ashfey's coat of arms. The crescent sun's light illuminates the study through this window. Magical lamps ensure no shadows remain.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Close the door behind you, boy," Duke Ashfey orders.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Andromeda can feel a fragment of his metaphorical mask fall away as his father speaks to him. He turns without complaint and shuts the door behind him. His father is a big man. His hulking figure is seated at an impressive oaken desk. A plethora of paperwork sits upon his desk.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Take a seat." Duke Ashfey gestures to a seat opposite his desk.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The cushioned chair does little to comfort Andromeda as he sits. He manages to force a wry grin onto his handsome face when his father looks at him. The fatherly nod of approval he gets does little to comfort him.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"I called you here to discuss your future," Duke Ashfey says ominously.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"My future? As the heir?" Andromeda questions.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Duke Ashfey nods his head slightly, but doesn't look fully certain of his answer. He slides a letter across his desk for Andromeda to read. The letter is written on expensive paper, and the distinct seal of the royal family is stamped onto the bottom.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"I'm getting engaged?"&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Indeed. King Goldenmane and I have worked out an agreement where both you and Cassandra will be paired with Lavender and Asmodeous. It will be the marriage alliance of the century!" Duke Ashfey explains with an excited shake of his fist.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Truly?" Andromeda questions.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Andromeda isn't really listening as his father goes on to explain the details of the engagement. His thoughts are a whirlwind. He can feel his emotional mask shattering into thousands of pieces as a reality he isn't ready to confront comes rushing headlong toward him.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;I can't let him see how I feel.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;i&gt;Keep your mask together, Andromeda!&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Duke Ashfey arches his brow at his son's strangely quiet behavior. Andromeda immediately flashes one of his signature grins to ease the tension in the room. He leans back and lets out a low whistle as if pleasantly surprised by the situation.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Father, for an uptight man you sure know how to make a boy happy."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;God, I feel like throwing up.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Duke Ashfey chuckles at his son's jest. He clears his throat, and takes on a stern tone.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"I'm sure I needn't remind you that you are not to do anything untoward with Princess Lavender before the ceremony?" Duke Ashfey questions threateningly.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"I was only making a joke, Father. I understand there are lines a man mustn't cross."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Good, good. Prince Asmodeous and Princess Lavender will be here tomorrow to meet with you and your sister, so be sure you're ready to woo her."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Andromeda's heart stops for a moment as the gravity of the situation sinks in. Every time he's been approached by a woman it's made his skin crawl. Andromeda silently swallows the lump in his throat.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Knock knock knock.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Duke Ashfey and Andromeda both turn to the door. Shortly after the knock, a maid announces herself.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"I have brought Princess Cassandra, as requested."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Duke Ashfey nods in satisfaction. He quickly motions for Andromeda to scoot to the side so his sister can join the conversation. Andromeda can feel his stomach churning as he does his best to piece his emotional mask back together.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"You're dismissed. Please enter, Cassandra," Duke Ashfey calls out.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The oaken doors to the study swing open to reveal Cassandra. Her silver hair is braided into a beautiful arrangement which hangs down her back. The glittering white dress she wears is the polar opposite of the training clothes she wore earlier. Her face is painted with makeup to appear more feminine, and she walks with the poise of a lady.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Greetings, Father."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Andromeda watches with a cloud of sadness swirling in his gut. His sister bows to Duke Ashfey to show her fealty. He nods and motions with his hand toward the open chair. She takes her seat with elegant motions that draw the eye to her gloved hands.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"I called you here to inform you that you'll be marrying Prince Asmodeous," Duke Ashfey states bluntly.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Cassandra's face twists as she fails to hide her emotions. Andromeda clicks his tongue as he watches his sister fail where he succeeded. Tears begin to well up in the corners of her eyes. Duke Ashfey doesn't even notice as he continues talking at her.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"You'll need to be on your best behavior for your first meeting. Tomorrow the prince will be here, and I expect you to treat him like a wife would her husband."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Andromeda's eyes catch the trembling of her hand. The tears start to pour down her face, and her makeup smudges as she lets out an audible sob. Duke Ashfey looks up at her with contempt marring his rugged features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Cassandra Clarice Ashfey," Duke Ashfey growls out her full name.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Cassandra tries to shakily wipe her eyes with the back of her gloved hands. Duke Ashfey stands from his chair and begins to unbuckle his belt. The metallic ting of the buckle slipping free gives Andromeda goosebumps.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"It seems you're still just a child, after all," Duke Ashfey sighs in his gravelly voice.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Andromeda watches his imposingly large father step around his oaken desk with a dark look in his eyes. Cassandra is shaking like a leaf as she knows what is coming. Andromeda stares at her with dead hollow eyes, and Cassandra turns to stare straight back at him. The plea for help in her grey eyes breaks something in Andromeda.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Duke Ashfey pulls his belt taught. He raises the strip of leather up with a grim frown. The leather snaps loudly as it's pulled tight enough to be used as a whip. Cassandra shuts her eyes and shields her face with her arms. Andromeda's ears are ringing.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;I'm sorry.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The impact Cassandra is expecting never comes. Duke Ashfey grunts as he tries to swing. Something is holding the belt back, and he can't whip Cassandra with it. He turns his head to see Andromeda standing there with a blank look on his handsome face.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"You've made a mistake, boy."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Andromeda looks up at his father without betraying his emotions. The empty look in his eyes shows no sadness. No anger. No fear. Duke Ashfey strikes Andromeda's chest with enough force to send him stumbling back. Andromeda stays standing.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"I should have known you were going to act up," Duke Ashfey sighs sadly.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The second blow comes down upon Andromeda's chest. This time he falls backwards and knocks over the chair he was sitting in moments earlier. Duke Ashfey clicks his tongue at his son, and puts his belt back on.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Andromeda lays there on the floor without moving for several moments. Duke Ashfey walks back around his desk, and takes his seat. The sound of his belt slipping back into place tells Andromeda he can finally stand.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;"Get out of my sight, Andromeda."&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The pain in his chest is immense as Andromeda stands. He carefully returns the chair back to its rightful place, and glances over at the chair Cassandra was sitting in. At some point during the beating she fled the room. Andromeda wordlessly leaves his father's study.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;I really blew it this time, huh?&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
